Document: AnimationNodeExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeextension.rst
Summary: Core methods for processing animation data and querying animation state in custom AnimationNode implementations.

Method: _process_animation_node(playback_info: PackedFloat64Array, test_only: bool) → PackedFloat32Array
A version of the AnimationNode._process() method meant to be overridden by custom nodes. Returns a PackedFloat32Array containing processed animation data. The playback_info parameter contains encoded playback information: playback time and delta, start/end times, seek request status (float > 0), external seek flag (float > 0), current LoopedFlag (encoded as float), and blend weight. The return array must contain animation length, time position, delta, LoopMode (encoded as float), animation end status (float > 0), and infinite status (float > 0).

Method: get_remaining_time(node_info: PackedFloat32Array, break_loop: bool) → float
Returns the animation's remaining time for the given node info. For looping animations, returns a large integer value unless break_loop is true, in which case it returns the actual remaining time.

Method: is_looping(node_info: PackedFloat32Array) → bool
Returns true if the animation for the given node_info is looping.